  <ThingDef ParentName="KP_Officer_Flak_Armor_Base">
    <defName>KP_Officer_Flak_Armor</defName>
    <label>Officer Carapace Armor</label>
    <description>Carapace Armor comes in many shapes and sizes, this variant however was designed in the factories of the Deathworld of Fury. Despite the name, Fury is a highly organized society with a caste system which maintains a highborn nobility and a lowborn servile class. Often under siege by the Insectoid fleets, the Furian Guard is subject to the same stratification as their cities. As the Officers of the Furian Guard are found among the nobility, they have access to this specific armor. Reinforced with additional plasteel and adorned with gold filagree which offers both protection and proof of status.</description>
    <graphicData>
      <texPath>Armor/OfficerArmorVariants/OfficerArmorBlank/OfficerArmor</texPath>
    </graphicData>
    <statBases>
      <WorkToMake>12000</WorkToMake>
      <MarketValue>1000</MarketValue>
      <MaxHitPoints>200</MaxHitPoints>
      <Mass>10.0</Mass>
      <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>1.15</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
      <EquipDelay>8</EquipDelay>
    </statBases>
    <apparel>
      <wornGraphicPath>Armor/OfficerArmorVariants/OfficerArmorBlank/OfficerArmor</wornGraphicPath>
      <tags Inherit="False">
        <li>BNF_Armor_Officer</li>
      </tags>
      <renderNodeProperties>
        <li Class="BNF.Core.DecalSystem.PawnRenderNodePropertiesOmniBnf">
          <nodeClass>VEF.Graphics.PawnRenderNode_Omni</nodeClass>
          <workerClass>BNF.Core.DecalSystem.PawnRenderNodeWorkerOmniBodyApparelBnf</workerClass>
          <parentTagDef>ApparelBody</parentTagDef>
          <baseLayer>16</baseLayer>

          <conditionalGraphics>
            <useFactionRNGSeed>true</useFactionRNGSeed>
            <texPaths>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/Captain</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/Crown</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/Hawk</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/Leaf Cluster</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/Lionhead</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/OfficerStar</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/StarBurst</li>
              <li>Symbols/Officer/Wreath</li>
            </texPaths>
            <colorA>
              <color>(0.0,0.0,0.0)</color>
            </colorA>
            <shader>Cutout</shader>
            <alts>
              <li>
                <tagRequirements>
                  <li>DecalActive</li>
                </tagRequirements>
                <texPath>DecalSymbol</texPath>
                <colorA>
                  <taggedColor>DecalSymbolColor</taggedColor>
                </colorA>
                <shader>Cutout</shader>
              </li>
            </alts>
          </conditionalGraphics>

          <visibleFacing>
            <li>South</li>
            <li>North</li>
          </visibleFacing>

          <BodyTypeOffsetsByFacingRows>
            <li>
              <bodyType>Fat</bodyType>
              <north>(0,0,0.07)</north>
              <south>(0,0,0.025)</south>
            </li>
            <li>
              <bodyType>Thin</bodyType>
              <north>(0,0,0.045)</north>
            </li>
            <li>
              <bodyType>Hulk</bodyType>
              <north>(0,0,0.7)</north>
              <south>(0,0,-0.07)</south>
            </li>
            <li>
              <bodyType>Female</bodyType>
              <north>(0,0,0.07)</north>
              <south>(0,0,0.05)</south>
            </li>
          </BodyTypeOffsetsByFacingRows>

          <drawData>
            <scale>0.085</scale>
            <defaultData>
              <layer>23.555</layer>
              <offset>(0,0,-0.20)</offset>
              <flip>true</flip>
            </defaultData>
            <dataNorth>
              <layer>23.384</layer>
              <offset>(0,0,-0.17)</offset>
            </dataNorth>
            <bodyTypeScales>
              <Hulk>1.55</Hulk>
              <Fat>1.35</Fat>
              <Thin>0.9</Thin>
              <Female>1.2</Female>
            </bodyTypeScales>
          </drawData>
        </li>
      </renderNodeProperties>
    </apparel>
    <modExtensions>
      <li Class="BNF.Core.DescriptionSwitcher.BnfDescriptionExtension">
        <LoreDesc>Carapace Armor was not the only design produced in the Great Domain. The expansive Officer Corps of the Inner Corp served as the Hand of the Dominion. Though unlike the millenia of wars before, Officers were commonly found in the wars which they fought. Inspired by the heroes of Ancient Earth, it was on the Deathworld of Fury where the
          Dominion Officer Corps designed this modified Carapace Armor. Forged with molecular reinforcement by the vast Furian forges, it was stronger and lighter for the Officers of the Dominion. When the Great Domain fell, the forges continued, arming the Furian Guard who took up the mantle of the Dominion in their sector.</LoreDesc>
        <VanillaDesc>A higher-quality variant of carapace armor, produced with refined methods for greater durability without extra weight. Features gold inlay as a symbol of rank and authority. Solid protection, but more ceremonial than frontline gear.</VanillaDesc>
      </li>
    </modExtensions>
  </ThingDef>

